sentence: U.S. stocks turned lower in volatile trading on Friday as worries about rising coronavirus cases and a patchy economic recovery dampened risk sentiment, with technology-related stocks reversing early gains to extend their declines to a third day.
ET, the Dow Jones Industrial Average .DJI was down 1.08% at 27,601.36, the S&P 500 .SPX was down 1.37% at 3,311.03 and the Nasdaq Composite .IXIC was down 1.67% at 10,727.702.
